'''Level 986''', dubbed "Baker-Miller Prison", “Pink-Colored Suffering” or “The Pink Prison”, is the 987th level of [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]]. It was discovered on March 14th, 1977 by several unknown explorers.
<div style="background:#dea2dd; color: #ffffff; border:3px solid #ff69fc; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #000000; padding:10px; margin:1em; text-align:left; text-align: center; border-radius: 0px 50px 0px 50px; font-family: Jost; font-size: 20px">'''Ꙫ  Description  Ꙫ'''</div>

{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Level 986 Cell.png|caption=A cell in '''Level 986'''.}}
'''Level 986''' is a collection of prison cells and halls, this prison is almost entirely pink-colored, specifically the Baker-Miller hue, excluding the flooring and metals. The level's layout appears to reformulate, and the entire process takes about a few seconds. Some cells are locked; the key to open them is typically near, lying on tables or the floor. These cells contain food and supplies, as a reward for the effort; bunk and regular beds are also found in pairs. Supplies and [[Object 2|Level Keys]] can also be found lying on desks. Curiously, in the cells, one can find a set of strange items, from lunch trays and clothes to bricks and dirty spoons, as if something was trying to escape. The cells on the level seem to lack bathroom items, and bathrooms themselves are separated from the cells. The bathrooms contain metal closets, retaining [[Object 1|Almond Water]].      

Wooden doors are typically entrances to offices or meeting rooms, with large and wide tables spread around them. Several items can be seen on the tables, such as papers of an investigative nature, cups of coffee, and bottles of hand sanitizer. Investigation rooms are a common theme on the level, being generally dimly lit. Their main feature is a large pinboard with photos on the wall, a small table with a cup of coffee, and papers. It is currently unknown what this investigation means.

{{Blurimage|align=right|caption=A hallway in '''Level 986'''.|file=Level 986 Hallway.png}}

Rare and anomalous vending machines that float are found around '''Level 986'''. These vending machines have various knock-off food and supplies. The foods in the machines vary, including bread, canned beans or meat, juice, and popcorn, among others. New products seem to materialize inside the device after one or all slots are unloaded. The vending machines fly nearby wanderers, being somewhat hidden. If there are no wanderers, it stays still. To receive fare from the machine, one needs a flat surface, like cloth or bland paper, to make a transaction.

While wandering around, one can find cafeterias. These have a buffet area, with drinks and food on display, sitting at a long wooden table. Wanderers report that the food in the buffet section has a rubberlike texture and is tasteless, as it never seems to rot. Besides the buffet, wanderers can find a metal door with a window leading to the kitchen; however, they are locked permanently, and wanderers cannot pass; they can only observe the kitchen from outside.

There are various air vents around '''Level 986'''; they vary in length and width. The winds in '''Level 986'''<nowiki/>'s air vents are fast and strong enough to launch a medium-sized being into the other side of the vent system, with fans boosting the wind speed. In most cases, it is impossible to crawl within the vents, as they are tight and easy to get stuck on; but also due to mold and other deadly fungi. The mold rapidly expands within the air vent system. Theorists suggest that this may infect the entire level, killing all living beings somewhere in the future. Stagnant water and several mysterious liquids around the air vents are common, and another reason one should not enter vents.

{{Blurimage|align=left|file=CoolDownPink.png|caption=A richer cell within '''Level 986'''.}}

Very few cells in '''Level 986''' appear to contain greater living conditions, these are often named "richer cells". They are more hygienic, have sinks, and even built-in bathrooms occasionally. These cells are also more comfortable, with beds with blankets and fluffy cushions. The richer cells, however, are all locked. The keys to them are more well-hidden than that of a common cell. These likewise contain forms of entertainment, like Rubik's cubes, papers for drawing, and ping pong. Counters are common in these cells, and supplies are found atop them, generally stocked in cardboard boxes. There are also indoor sports rooms which are quite uncommon, too, these contain varied sports items, like rackets, paddles, nets, balls, etc.    

Staying for a long amount of time in '''Level 986''' will cause several mental illnesses, like Alzheimer's and dementia. However, the most notable of these is known as "Pink Insanity", a highly perilous and common malady caused by staring into pink. This disorder may be mitigated through meditation. This condition can be avoided by not looking at the level's pink hue. If one carries this illness for an extended time, it will become contagious. Below are the symptoms of the illness.
