{{Blurimage|align=right|caption=A therapy room in '''Level 986'''.|file=Therapiss.jpg}}
Therapy rooms are rare finds on '''Level 986''', and they are the only area on the level that is not thoroughly pink. A stay in a therapy room strikes wanderers with immense comfort, which improves their sanity. When any living being is inside one of these rooms, the door is "locked" from the inside, and no other being may enter the room. Strangely, the door only behaves as if it is locked from the outside, and the person inside the room can open it at any time without any keys.

Around the level, one can find a series of journals, named "The Baker-Miller Archives", featuring the infamous quote "Mind reading?" on the covers. The journals tell the entire history of the level, properties, entities, and phenomena yet to be discovered, logs, and tips. It is believed there are seven or more journals on the level, with only three found so far. The journals are currently protected property of the [[M.E.G.]], heavily guarded in the depths of their headquarters. According to the physical description of the journals described by Auto Nexus historians, the journals' covers seem to be Bake-Miller pink, with a slight gray shade in each corner. The [[M.E.G.]] requests anyone who encounters a journal to donate it for "educational" purposes. An alternative series of newspapers is distributed around the level, as a form of illusion to anyone who finds them. These newspapers are filled with false information and humorous comics. Being immensely less valued than the journals, these newspapers serve as one of the primary staples of entertainment on the level.

<div style="background:#dea2dd; color: #ffffff; border:3px solid #ff69fc; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #000000; padding:10px; margin:1em; text-align:left; text-align: center; border-radius: 0px 50px 0px 50px; font-family: Jost; font-size: 20px">'''Ꙫ  Entities Ꙫ'''</div>
In '''Level 986''', [[The Armless]] may be found as the most common entity, [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]], [[Foams]], and [[Kats]] may also rarely be found within the level. Entities in '''Level 986''' manifest as hallucinations before materializing, these "entities" are known as Pink Manifestations. Other level-exclusive entities inhabit '''Level 986'''.
=== Pink Manifestations ===
{{Collapse|initial=Open Pink Manifestation Info.|num=2|final=Close Pink Manifestation Info.|body={{Entity Class|Agg=0|Int=1|Dan=0|Hab=Level 986|no=???}}
{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Level 986 Pink Manifestations.png|caption=A witness's sketch of a Pink Manifestation.}}
Pink Manifestations are a controversial topic, while some affirm it is an entity, others affirm it is a mental illness symptom. Their life span is about two months; after that time, they will become one entity in a determined set. Generally, these creatures take the form of whatever entity they will become, albeit distorted and strangely colored. Pink Manifestations are not physical, but they can quicken up the evolution process by absorbing raw energy and gases. These creatures can become visible and invisible at random times, but typically near energy. Staying near them will cause one to develop irreversible mental illnesses, such as schizophrenia, bipolar, Down syndrome, etc.}}
===Pink Guards===
{{Collapse|num=3|initial=Open Pink Guards Info.|final=Close Pink Guards Info.|body={{Entity Class|Agg=3|Int=5|Dan=5|Hab=Level 986|no=???}}
Pink Guards is a very rare entity found within '''Level 986'''. They resemble tall, strong, pink beings that hold large weapons. They are additionally typically described as having a rock-like body. Pink Guards patrol an area of 30 square kilometers within '''Level 986''', looking for threats and anomalies. If a Pink Guard encounters a wanderer, it will examine the wanderer's appearance and mind, if prompted by a threat, the Pink Guard will rip the person from the inside out. Pink Guards have a lifetime of 100 years and will implode after, leaving stains around the area.}}
===Bake-Miller===
{{Collapse|initial=Open Bake-Miller Info.|final=Close Bake-Miller Info.|num=986|body={{Entity Class|Agg=4|Int=5|Dan=5|Hab=Level 986|no=???}}
Bake-Miller is a highly intelligent, perilous entity. It takes on the appearance of an arachnid with human-like skin. It crawls and thrives in the air vents of the level. Bake-Miller is very strong and resistant, being nearly immortal. It has presumably been alive for centuries. Bake-Miller can breathe the mold from the air vents, contributing to its long-term survival. Bake-Miller's diet mainly consists of humans and mold. Bake-Miller devours humans due to its despise for them, a reason the [[M.E.G.]] imprisons it within the air vents at the heart of the level. As time passed, as a result of Bake-Miller's great senses of smelling, seeing, and hearing, it quickly learned the English language. Since then, it has tried to deceive members of the [[M.E.G.]] to free it.}}
